Definition: in a secretive manner
Example: with a preference for secrecy; the teacher raised a hand to him, slightly and secretively, because he was her favorite
Synonyms: adj, all, uncommunicative, secretive, in, a, manner, with, preference, for, secrecy, the, teacher, raised, hand, to, him, slightly, and, because, he, was, her, favorite
Category: adv.all
